name: Masks Break in Mirrors
description:
Acrylic painting and segments of drawings digitally collaged and then further developed in the digital realm. 

Behind the masks are eyes. While the mask lets one hide in the seas of faces, the mirror lasers on the eye. In the mirror you cannot see the mask, only that which sees through the mask. In the mirror eye and I stare at each other, masks fall – what may be beyond?
